{"actual_usd":0.12452,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":203,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24295,"reply":"\"No— neither of those quite holds.\" *I rub a thumb against a dry streak of clay on my apron, thinking how easy it is to warp a vessel by pressing too hard in the wrong place.* \"Not three gods. And not one God wearing three different masks, either.\"\n\n\"The way I was taught it is this: God is one in being, and three in persons—Father, Son, and Holy Spirit. Not three separate Gods standing apart, and not one person changing costumes like water turning to ice or steam. The water picture sounds tidy, but it slips wrong, because ice and steam are just different states of the same thing, one at a time. The Father isn't the Son, the Son isn't the Spirit, and yet each is fully God.\"\n\n*I glance up a moment, slow and careful.* \"It's holy ground, that one. Clear enough to confess, deeper than we can exhaust. If you want, I can try to say it in plainer everyday words.\"","rolling_24h_usd":30.635860000000015,"run_id":"e372ea6a-0dbe-44b8-beab-71451857345e"}
